    </section>

    <section class="block2">
      <div class="container about-flex-container">
        <div class="about-text-wrapper">
          <h3 class="sub-title">History</h3>
          <p>
            What began as a childhood curiosity has grown into a passion for
            designing spaces that feel alive and tell their own stories. My
            journey in interior design has been about blending beauty with
            comfort, creating rooms that don’t just look elegant but also feel
            warm and meaningful. Every project is a chance to turn everyday
            spaces into places where memories are made and life feels a little
            more inspiring.
            <br /><span class="quotes"
              >“Designing spaces, crafting emotions, and shaping
              stories within walls.”</span
            >
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-image-wrapper">
          <img
            src="https://res.cloudinary.com/daoju0r3c/image/upload/v1754990315/STUDY_AREA_15A3_CAMBRIDGE_COURT_4.jpeg_vu9fuc.jpg"
            alt="Beautiful living room"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block2 my-4 py-3">
      <div class="fixed-bg bg1"></div>
      <div class="container about-flex-container about-me-layout">
        <div class="about-image-wrapper">
          <img
            src="https://res.cloudinary.com/daoju0r3c/image/upload/v1753411964/founder_xvmucl.jpg"
            alt="Founder"
          />
          <div class="image-caption">
            <h3>Charmi Gogri</h3>
            <span><h4>Founder</h4></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-text-wrapper">
          <h3 class="sub-title">About Me</h3>
          <p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8;">
            My journey in interior design began with a childhood fascination for
            transforming empty rooms into inviting spaces, which led to two
            years of formal education in the field. I then gained three years of
            hands-on experience at a leading interior and architecture firm,
            focusing on site execution and project management. In 2016, I
            launched my first firm, starting solo and eventually building a team
            of five, united by a shared commitment to thoughtful, functional
            design. A transformative three-year period in Hong Kong exposed me
            to a rich blend of traditional and modern aesthetics, enhancing my
            ability to work across diverse markets. In 2022, I founded my second
            firm with a clear vision: to create interiors that do more than
            appeal visually—they should feel right and support well-being. I
            approach each project with the belief that design deeply influences
            how we live, aiming to shape spaces that inspire, uplift, and
            connect.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="block2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="arch-section">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
              <h3 class="sub-title m-0">
                Architects <br />with different approach
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8">
              <div class="our-awards-sec">
                <div class="row" style="justify-content: center;">
                  <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-3 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="award-col">
                      <h2 class="count">34</h2>
                      <h3>Number Of Sites</h3>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6">
                    <div class="award-col">
                      <h2 class="count">12</h2>
                      <h3>Years Experience</h3>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      function animateCountUp(element) {
        const finalCount = parseInt(element.textContent, 10);
        const duration = 4000;
        let startTime = null;

        const step = (timestamp) => {
          if (!startTime) startTime = timestamp;
          const progress = timestamp - startTime;
          const current = Math.min(
            Math.floor((progress / duration) * finalCount),
            finalCount
          );
          element.textContent = current;

          if (progress < duration) {
            window.requestAnimationFrame(step);
          } else {
            element.textContent = finalCount;
          }
        };
        window.requestAnimationFrame(step);
      }

      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries, observer) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              const counters = entry.target.querySelectorAll(".count");
              counters.forEach((counter) => {
                animateCountUp(counter);
              });
              observer.unobserve(entry.target);
            }
          });
        },
        {
          threshold: 0.5,
        }
      );

      const sectionToWatch = document.querySelector(".arch-section");
      if (sectionToWatch) {
        observer.observe(sectionToWatch);
      }
    </script>

    <section class="vision-sec py-5">
      <div class="fixed-bg bg1"></div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
          <div class="col-lg-7">
            <div class="custom-image-layout">
